text: Shit, this brings many memories back, even if the game wasn't super balanced and it was super grindy, it was still a great game, the people that played it made it super fun and I still think about some of my Maple friends every once in a while. I remember trying to do a PQ and spending hours trying to get enough people to do it, and since there wasn't much to do while waiting, you'd chat with the guys you already found or the members of your guild, or going to Henesys to see your friends because you got bored of leveling and you just wanted to chill and mess around, I don't regret any minute I spent playing this game, even if it was P2W and super imba lol .

author: Luculyia de Voltazux

text:
@SupraDarky The fact that they have added story modes to EVERY class that you choose honestly does make it better.  I just finished the Adventurer's story mode (finishes once you hit level 100) and it was rather enjoyable for an mmorpg at least.

The newer tracks, while some are good, kinda feel like they lack the same charm that the tracks from when the game first came out did.  Lith Harbour is still one of the best tracks, and the song that plays in the slime tree was honestly enjoyable.  The new stuff is starting to sound like typical MMO fanfare, while the original music kinda was in a league of its own for an mmo.
